    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean equals(java.lang.Object obj)
      Implementations of the IdReferenceMatch interface must override the equals method with the following semantics: Two IdReferenceMatch objects (i1 and i2) are equal if: i1.getId().equals(i2.getId()) AND i1.getVersion() == null && i2.getVersion() == null OR i1.getVersion().equals(i2.getVersion()) i1.getEarliestVersion() == null && i2.getEarliestVersion() == null OR i1.getEarliestVersion().equals(i2.getEarliestVersion()) AND i1.getLatestVersion() == null && i2.getLatestVersion() == null OR i1.getLatestVersion().equals(i2.getLatestVersion())

    • Constructor Detail

      • StdIdReferenceMatch

        public StdIdReferenceMatch(Identifier idIn,
                   VersionMatch versionIn,
                   VersionMatch earliestVersionIn,
                   VersionMatch latestVersionIn)
        Creates a new StdIdReferenceMatch with the given Identifier representing the PolicyId or PolicySetId to match, and the given set of VersionMatch objects specifying which XACML Versions are acceptable.
        Parameters:
        idIn - the Identifier representing the PolicyId or PolicySetId.
        versionIn - the VersionMatch for an exact match against the current Version of a Policy or PolicySet (may be null)
        earliestVersionIn - the VersionMatch for a lower-bound match against the current Version of a Policy or PolicySet (may be null)
        latestVersionIn - the VersionMatch for an upper-bound match against the current Version of a Policy or PolicySet (may be null)
